Hey BC actor peeps! Little update. After a lot of thought and support, I’ve decided to run for a director position in the UBCP/ACTRA @ubcp_actra Executive Board!!! After working with so many incredible people in the BIPOC committee, and seeing just how much can be achieved when we all stand together, I’d love the opportunity to help push our industry forward. 

Check out my candidate statement below and if you’d love to share this post and show your support, I’d be over the moon! Also if you have any questions for me or would love to chat, please reach out or comment below on what you’d want to see UBCP tackle. This is a little outside my comfort zone so thank you to all the amazing humans (special shout-out to @angela_moore111) for the extra push to believe in myself. ♥️

CANDIDATE STATEMENT: 
Hi everyone! I’m Aliza. As a working actor and member of the union for over 15 years, and recently working alongside the UBCP BIPOC committee in championing positive change for our equity seeking members, I have accumulated a great deal of insight into the many ways our industry has flourished but also the many changes that have impacted us over the last few years. These include our changes in the audition process, opportunity to create and collaborate on a multitude of platforms, and our evolving world of technology in filmmaking. I want to make BC an undeniable force in the storytelling world and to entice filmmakers back to this province so that their work can benefit from our skills and experience and vice versa. As a person who is passionate about solving problems, I will aim to listen and advocate for swift actionable change that our membership can see. My goal isn’t just to help our working members on set but our members who work every day in this industry in pursuit of their next project or who may not be getting the full support needed to succeed in entertainment. If given the privilege to serve on the Executive Board this term, I hope to revitalize the BC film industry to reflect the creativity of the artists and performers present and to empower them to create, collaborate, and innovate!

#ubcpactra #ubcp #boardelections #actorlife #representationmatters #bipoc

Well, 32 is here in the blink of an eye. I usually try to find something new to focus in every year. My hope is that I can explore new things and get outside my comfort zone this year. 

Something I’ve learned about myself recently is that even when I believe I’ve simplified my life in pursuit of an anxiety free existence, I find myself taking on new challenges and jumping right back into something else. But the truth is, it really is in my nature to find new ideas to explore and find new challenges that can teach me more about myself. It really does give me so much joy and purpose and I hope that never changes. So…this year, maybe I’ll be able to find balance…maybe… Let’s find out. 😂 Either way, I’m excited for what this year has in store.
